In real life, when several objectives are optimized, conflicts will happen. When the solution of one objective is improved, it may harm the other objectives. Multi-objective optimization is an optimization process of finding solutions optimizing all objectives as much as possible. The solution set of multi-objective optimization problem is called Pareto optimal solution set, which was first put forward by a Italian economist Pareto in 1906 [43]. Finding a set of solutions is the ultimate goal of Pareto optimal process. The multi-objective optimization problem (MOP) is described as follows: There are p inequality constraints and q equality constraints.6\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
